<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.283165>
    bibo:endPage "62" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:startPage "51" ;
    bibo:volume "3590" ;
    dc:creator "Kononenko, Vladimir S.; Volynkin, Anton V.; Yu, Alexei" ;
    dc:date "2012" ;
    dc:title "A revision of the Xestia (Radddea) alexis (Kozhanchikov, 1928) species-group with a checklist of subgenus Raddea Alphéraky, 1892 and description of brachipterous females (Lepidoptera, Noctuidae, Noctuinae)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.283166>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.283167>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.283168>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.283169> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.283166>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1 – 6. 1, 2. Original description and illustration of Agrotis oschi (after Bang-Haas 1922); 3. X. alexis specimen, marked by Staudinger as “ Agrotis oschi ”; 4. X. alexis, holotype; 5. X. alexis (holotype of Estimata militzae); 6. Xestia herrichschaefferi, lectotype." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/283166/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.283167>
    dc:description "FIGURES 7 – 32. 7. Xestia alexis, female, Altai (right—dorsal view, left—lateral view); 8. X. herrichschaefferi, female, Altai (right—dorsal view, left—lateral view); 9 – 16. Series of males of X. alexis, showing variability of the species; 17 – 24. Series of males of X. herrichschaefferi, showing variability of the species; 25 – 32. Northern species of the genus Xestia, subgenus Pachnobia with brachypterous females. 25, 26 — X. aequava, 27, 28 — X. alaskae; 29, 30 — X. liquidaria; 31, 32 — X. kurentzovi (right male, left female)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/283167/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.283168>
    dc:description "FIGURES 33 – 38. Xestia (Raddea) spp., male genitalia: 33. X. alexis, specimen, indicated by Staudinger as “ oschi ”. Altai. Genit. prep. MB 150 Ch. Boursin; 34. X. alexis, Altai, lectotype, genit. prep.; 35. X. alexis, Altai, holotype of militzae, genit. prep.; 36. X. herrichschaefferi, Mongolia, Ulan Baator, lectotype, genit. prep.; Female genitalia: 37. X. alexis, Altai, genit. prep. VK- 23 - 221211; 38. X. herrichschaefferi, Altai, genit. prep. VK- 24 - 221211." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/283168/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.283169>
    dc:description "FIGURES 39 – 43. Habitats and distribution map of X. alexis and X. herrichschaefferi. 39. Altai, Aktash, 2600 m., montane tundra with Dryas oxyodonta, habitat of X. alexis; 40. Altai, shore of Ukok lake, 2300 m., montane tundra, habitat of X. alexis; 41. Altai, Sailugem, 2300 m, dry montane steppe, habitat of X. herrichschaefferi. 42. Male of X. alexis feeding on flowers of Bistorta elliptica (Polygonaceae) at daytime; 43. Distribution map of X. alexis (red) and X. herrichschaefferi (blue)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/283169/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

